de.esoco.lib.model

Class ListDataProvider<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.esoco.lib.model.AbstractDataProvider<T>
      • de.esoco.lib.model.ListDataProvider<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataProvider<T>, HasAttributeFilter<T>, HasAttributeSorting<T>

    public class ListDataProvider<T>
extends AbstractDataProvider<T>
    A DataProvider implementation that is backed by a List. It also implements ordering and filtering on attributes of the contained data.

        public java.util.Collection<T> getData(int nStart,
                                       int nCount)
        Returns a subset of data objects from this provider. If less data then requested is available the returned collection may contain less elements then nCount. It may even be empty but it will never be NULL.
        Parameters:
        nStart - The starting index of the first data object to return
        nCount - The number of data objects to return
        Returns:
        A collection of data objects (may be empty but will never be NULL)
